Geographic Location: USA: Sippewissett Salt Marsh, Falmouth, MA
Comments: Pink berry microbial consortia are a macroscopic microbial aggregates dominated by sulfur cycling species - the purple sulfur bacteria Thiohalocapsa PB-PSB1 and the sulfate reducer Desulfofustis PB-SRB1. The present study deeply sequenced these consortia with both PacBio sequencing platforms. Samples collected in 2011 from Little Sippewissett 'pond 01'

Isolation Source: pink berry consortia of the Sippewissett salt marsh
Geographic Location: USA: Sippewissett Marsh, Cape Cod, MA
Comments: Assembled metagenomic scaffolds that have been binned using tetranucleotide-frequency emergent self organizing maps. This genomic bin has been identified as an uncultured Thiohalocapsa species PB-PSB1, the purple sulfur bacterial species that composes the majority of the biomass in the pink berry consortia of the Sippewissett salt marsh.

Sequencing Center: Institute for Biodiversity and Ecosystem dynamics, Faculty of Science, University of Amsterdam
Comments: In this study we examined the vertical distribution of genes and transcripts originating from dissimilatory sulfur-cycling prokaryotes in the water and surface sediments of Cock soda lake, a relatively large hypersaline soda lake in the Kulunda Steppe (South-Western Siberia, Russian Federation).

Sequencing Center: Federal University of Rio de Janeiro
Comments: In order to investigate the taxonomic diversity and the metabolic potential of microorganisms in the hypersaline lagoon system of Araruama (HLSA, Brazil), one of the largest in the world, we sequenced metagenomes of microbial mats and assembled microbial genomes from the generated sequencing data.

Isolation Source: rhizosphere of the salt marsh grasses

Isolation Comments: isolated from anoxic sediment in a marine aquaculture pond near Bheemli (India)
Comments: Thiohalocapsa marina is a phototrophic, purple sulfur bacterium originally isolated from anoxic sediment in a marine aquaculture pond near Bheemli (India). We now sequenced the whole genome sequence of the type strain JA142T (=JCM 14780T=DSM 19078T).

Sequencing Center: GEOMAR Helmholtz Centre for Ocean Research Kiel
Comments: Sequencing and assembly of draft genomes of cultured anoxygenic phototrophic bacteria

Using next generation sequencing, large amounts of metagenomic data have been generated from aquatic environments. However, a huge amount of the aquatic prokaryotic repertoire is still undefined. Here we identified 1504 uncultured prokaryotic aquatic species by reconstructing metagenome-assembled genomes (MAGs) from publicly available sequence data.
